# Environment Configuration for TutorPlatform Frontend

# Development Environment
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080

# Production Environment Examples:
# For HTTPS deployment, use your actual backend domain:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://backend.yourapp.herokuapp.com
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend-vercel-url.vercel.app

# Important Notes for Production Deployment:
# 1. Make sure frontend and backend are on HTTPS
# 2. Configure CORS on backend to allow your frontend domain
# 3. Set proper cookie settings for cross-origin requests:
#    - SameSite=None (for cross-origin)
#    - Secure=true (for HTTPS)
#    - HttpOnly=true (recommended for security)
# 4. In deployment platform (Vercel, Netlify, etc.), set:
#    NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend-domain.com